info.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 18 at 3:24AM EST until December 19 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Caribou
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM THIS MORNING TO 1 AM EST TUESDAY... * WHAT...South winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 70 mph along the coast...and to 60 mph inland...expected. * WHERE...Southern Penobscot, Interior Hancock, Central Washington, Coastal Hancock and Coastal Washington Counties. * WHEN...From 7 AM this morning to 1 AM EST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and powerlines. Numerous to widespread power outages are likely. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. Use caution if you must drive.
